An emotional memorial service for two of the 21 teenagers who died at the eNyobeni tavern in East London was held on Tuesday. eNCA's Aviwe Mtila reports. #DStv403 EAST LONDON - An emotional memorial service for two of the 21 teenagers who died at the eNyobeni tavern in East London was held on Tuesday. On Wednesday, a mass funeral service will be held for the victims of the tragedy. READ: Tavern Tragedy | Preparations underway for mass funeral President Cyril Ramaphosa is expected to attend the funeral. Meanwhile, Eastern Cape Premier Oscar Mabuyane says collective responsibility must be taken for the tragedy. READ: Tavern tragedy | Authorities clamp down on non-compliance Mabuyane also says the liquor board and police can't be blamed as the tavern had a liquor license. * eNCA's Aviwe Mtila reports.